I appreciate you sharing this. I had a similar problem. Trichotillomania is what I suffered from for many years. Hair pulling was a very serious problem to the point where I had to cut my hair down from about a 12 inches to about half an inch. Keeping my hair short except on the top is the only way Iâ€™ve really found to not give myself any triggers. But stress is a very big motivator in pulling my hair out. In fact, I actually found that while stress is a very big part of my life, having control over certain things is fundamental to my mental health. Realizing that I donâ€™t look half-bad with a Brendon Urie haircut was a nice little boost too. Anything to keep my neuroses down to a tolerable level. I really wish you the best of luck with this. *hugs*
